quran[11]{c,v,t}:
  39,11,"Say; ‘I am commanded to worship God, consecrating my religion to Him"
  39,12,I am commanded to be the first of Muslims.‘
  39,13,"Say: ‘I fear, if I disobey my Lord, the torment of a fateful day"
  39,14,"Say: ‘God I worship, consecrating my religion to Him"
  39,15,"As for yourselves, worship what you will besides Him.‘ Say: ‘They shall lose much, those who will forfeit their souls and their kin on the Day of Resurrection. That will surely be the ultimate loss"
  39,16,"Above them there shall be sheets of fire, and sheets of fire shall be beneath them. By this, God puts fear into His servants‘ hearts.‘ Fear Me, then, My servants"
  39,17,But those who keep from idol-worship and turn to God in penitence shall rejoice; give joyful tidings to My servants
  39,18,who listen to precepts and follow what is best in them. It is these whom God has guided; it is these that are of good sense possessed
  39,19,Can you rescue from the Fire those on whom the Word of torment was pronounced
  39,20,"As for those who truly fear their Lord, they shall be lodged in mansions towering high, set about with running brooks. Such is God‘s promise: God never fails His promise"
  39,21,"Do you not see how God sends down water from the sky which penetrates the earth and gathers in springs beneath? With it He then brings forth plants of various hues. They wither, they turn yellow, and then He turns them into dust. Surely in this there is an admonition for those that are of good sense possessed"